-- Infineon’s Bauer Sees Mild Drop in 2012 Sales, WamS Reports
-- B y   B r i a n   P a r k i n
-- 2012-06-03T13:50:44Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-06-03/infineon-s-bauer-sees-mild-drop-in-2012-sales-wams-reports.html
German semi-conductor maker  Infineon
Technologies AG (IFX)  expects only a “slight” drop in sales this
year compared with 2011,  Welt-am-Sonntag  reported, citing an
interview with Chief Executive Officer  Peter Bauer .  Orders for the third quarter are running “very well,”
particularly in power-management electronics for computers and
for  consumer goods , Bauer is cited as saying. Orders from
southern Europe for electronic products for industry are “very
weak” and orders in this segment from China and  India 
“relatively flat,” he said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Brian Parkin in Berlin at 
 bparkin@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
James Hertling at 
